About this channel:
This channel is a result of a younger boy who didn't have much to do besides playing games and occasionally playing around with editing softwares and his in-game recordings. Most of what you see here is self-taught. I did study towards a media-based secondary education, but what I learned from that was not something I could implement in these videos on this channel.

This channel will always be my little playground, though. Games and neat effects, pretty much. My more "professional" productions will be published somewhere elsewhere.

About me:
My name is Thomas. I used to work as a Motion Graphic Artist in Oslo, Norway, and in pre-press in a printing company. My passion is graphics, interactive media and film. That's what I want to do and it's that kind of work that suits me as a person.

Thank you for viewing my work and don't hesitate to contact me if you need help or need me for some project.

This marked the beginning of the rise of a future legend ‚Äì Danil ‚ÄúDendi‚Äù Ishutin. Since 2018, the squad has been led by the experienced captain SoNNeikO, who's already played under the yellow and black banner before. 
NAVI have repeatedly participated in major tournaments like TI, DreamLeague, EPICENTER, ESL One, SL i-League, The Summit. 
Nowadays, NAVI.DOTA2 is one of the most popular and recognizable CIS teams.

PingSkills produces Table Tennis coaching tutorials to help you improve your game. We regularly add videos on the strokes and techniques of the game plus we record video responses to questions we've received through the ask the coach section of the PingSkills website. We also produce a weekly podcast where we answer your table tennis questions.

Alois Rosario is the head coach with decades of experience in coaching. He was also a very good player himself representing Australia at multiple World Championships. He is currently the coach of the Australian Paralympic team.

Jeff Plumb is the video editor and website developer at PingSkills. Jeff represented Australia at the Sydney 2000 Olympic Games and is currently studying to become a mathematics and IT teacher.

If you want to let us help you improve your table tennis then subscribe to our channel.

To improve your table tennis visit http://www.PingSkills.com/

Recombu serves up reviews, unboxings and in-depth features on the latest UK mobile tech, revealing the best smartphones for every budget.

We show you the best bits in our in-depth guides, test out the biggest features such as a smartphone's camera or performance, and compare with rivals to show which is best for you. You can also watch our live coverage of tech launches, and our long-term reviews of the most popular gadgets.

Subscribe and tap that notifications bell to be the first to watch our tech coverage - and please say hi!

snippet.description:
About this channel:
This channel is a result of a younger boy who didn't have much to do besides playing games and occasionally playing around with editing softwares and his in-game recordings. Most of what you see here is self-taught. I did study towards a media-based secondary education, but what I learned from that was not something I could implement in these videos on this channel.

This channel will always be my little playground, though. Games and neat effects, pretty much. My more "professional" productions will be published somewhere elsewhere.

About me:
My name is Thomas. I used to work as a Motion Graphic Artist in Oslo, Norway, and in pre-press in a printing company. My passion is graphics, interactive media and film. That's what I want to do and it's that kind of work that suits me as a person.

Thank you for viewing my work and don't hesitate to contact me if you need help or need me for some project.

snippet.description:
PingSkills produces Table Tennis coaching tutorials to help you improve your game. We regularly add videos on the strokes and techniques of the game plus we record video responses to questions we've received through the ask the coach section of the PingSkills website. We also produce a weekly podcast where we answer your table tennis questions.

Alois Rosario is the head coach with decades of experience in coaching. He was also a very good player himself representing Australia at multiple World Championships. He is currently the coach of the Australian Paralympic team.

Jeff Plumb is the video editor and website developer at PingSkills. Jeff represented Australia at the Sydney 2000 Olympic Games and is currently studying to become a mathematics and IT teacher.

If you want to let us help you improve your table tennis then subscribe to our channel.

To improve your table tennis visit http://www.PingSkills.com/

PingSkills produces Table Tennis coaching tutorials to help you improve your game. We regularly add videos on the strokes and techniques of the game plus we record video responses to questions we've received through the ask the coach section of the PingSkills website. We also produce a weekly podcast where we answer your table tennis questions.

Alois Rosario is the head coach with decades of experience in coaching. He was also a very good player himself representing Australia at multiple World Championships. He is currently the coach of the Australian Paralympic team.

Jeff Plumb is the video editor and website developer at PingSkills. Jeff represented Australia at the Sydney 2000 Olympic Games and is currently studying to become a mathematics and IT teacher.

If you want to let us help you improve your table tennis then subscribe to our channel.

To improve your table tennis visit http://www.PingSkills.com/
